$ X.500

X.500 is a series of computer networking standards covering electronic Directory Services.


{ TODO

  Directory services based on X.500 inlude
    • Microsoft's Active Directory
    • → development/web/protocols/LDAP[Lightweight Directory Access Protocol] (LDAP)
    • Novell eDirectory
    • Siemens DirX
  The Domain Name System (DNS) is a directory service which is not based on X.500.

  → development/security/cryptography/X_509 was originally intended to be based on X.500.

  There are two kinds of objects
    • Organisational Units (OU), which is a container object
    • Leaf objects, which are contained in containers (CN, UID, etc.)

  ? A → development/web/protocols/X_500/distinguished-name[distinguished name] identifies an object in the directory information tree (DIT).

  → https://www.iso.org/standard/80313.html[ISO/IEC 9594-1:2020] Information technology — Open systems interconnection — Part 1: The Directory: Overview of concepts, models and services

